    "objectID": "session1/index.html#what-is-bioinformatics",
    "href": "session1/index.html#what-is-bioinformatics",
    "title": "Introduction to Bioinformatics",
    "section": "What is Bioinformatics?",
    "text": "What is Bioinformatics?\n\nbioinformatics\n\ndoing computer science / software engineering\nusing your knowledge of biology\n\ncomputational biology\n\ndoing biology\nusing your knowledge of computational techniques"
  },
  {
    "objectID": "session1/index.html#areas-of-biology",
    "href": "session1/index.html#areas-of-biology",
    "title": "Introduction to Bioinformatics",
    "section": "Areas of Biology",
    "text": "Areas of Biology\n\nSpecies level\n\nzoology, botony, evolutionary biology, microbiology (bacteriology, virology)\n\nOrganism level\n\nanatomy, physiology, immunology / kinesiology / hematology / neurobiology\n\nTissue / Cell level\n\nhistology, cell biology, developmental biology, embryology / gerontology\n\nDNA / RNA / Protein level\n\ngenetics, genomics, transcriptomics, proteomics, metabolomics, epigenetics, metagenomics, phylogenomics, population genetics\n\nMolecular level\n\nmolecular biology, structural biology, biochemistry, biophysics\n\nDisease / Therapeutics level\n\nbiomedical research, epidemiology, pathology, pharmacology"
  },
