  {
    "objectID": "intro-to-bioinfo.html",
    "href": "intro-to-bioinfo.html",
    "title": "Introduction to Bioinformatics",
    "section": "",
    "text": "This set of presentations was originally part of an effort, in 2016, to present a very high-level overview of biology and bioinformatics to professional software developers. I’m recreating this, in 2025, as a quarto website that contains the quarto presentations (and posting on Github with auto-deployment)."
  },
  {
    "objectID": "intro-to-bioinfo.html#part-1---biology-down-to-the-cell",
    "href": "intro-to-bioinfo.html#part-1---biology-down-to-the-cell",
    "title": "Introduction to Bioinformatics",
    "section": "Part 1 - Biology “down to the cell”",
    "text": "Part 1 - Biology “down to the cell”\nThis session discusses what is biology and bioinformatics and moves us from “all of life” down to the cell level.\nTopics include:\n\nWhat is Bioinformatics?\nAreas of Biology\nZoology / Species / Model Organisms\nAnatomy / Tissues / Cells\nCell Biology\nCell Development / Differentiation"
  },
  {
    "objectID": "intro-to-bioinfo.html#part-2----omics-molecular-structural-biology",
    "href": "intro-to-bioinfo.html#part-2----omics-molecular-structural-biology",
    "title": "Introduction to Bioinformatics",
    "section": "Part 2 - “-omics”, Molecular / Structural biology",
    "text": "Part 2 - “-omics”, Molecular / Structural biology\nThis is the main part and is divided into three sessions. The goal is to cover the biology related to various “-omics” topics.\n\nSession 2a - Genomics / DNA and Transcriptomics / RNA\nThis session includes:\n\nCentral Dogma\n\nTranscription / Translation\nCanonical Gene Model\n\nGenomics / DNA\n\nSequences, Assemblies, Features and Feature Sets\nDatabases / File Formats\nBioinformatics Algorithms\nSequencing in the lab\n\nTranscriptomics / RNA\n\nTypes of RNA\nMeasuring expression levels\n\n\n\n\nSession 2b - Proteomics, Metabolomics, and Variants\nThis session includes:\n\nProteomics / Proteins\n\nTranslation and Post-translational Modifications\nProtein Structure\nExpression and Localization\nInteraction and Function\n\nMetabolomics / Metabolites\nVariants / Mutations\n\nTypes of Variants\nVariant Calling / Algorithms\nConsequence Prediction\n\n\n\n\nSession 2c - Regulation, RNAi, and Epigenetics\nThis session includes:\n\nRegulation / RNAi\n\nEnhancers, Silencers, and Transcription Factors\nRNAi - miRNA and siRNA\nKnockdowns and Knockouts - shRNA and CRISPR\n\nEpigenetics\n\nDNA methylation\nHistone modification\n\nMetagenomics\nPhylogenomics"
